          <p class="text-body text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Theory is useful. Shipping is better. Five steps to your first hierarchical multi-agent system:
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
            <div class="diagram-node rounded-xl border border-green/20 p-5 bg-elevated hover:bg-green/5 transition-colors">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
                <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-green/10 flex items-center justify-center text-green font-mono text-sm border border-green/30">1</span>
                <h3 class="text-foreground font-medium">Define the Contract</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-small text-secondary ml-11">Typed payloads between agents: what goes in, what comes out, what errors look like.</p>
              <div class="ml-11 mt-2 bg-subtle rounded p-3 font-mono text-xs text-secondary overflow-x-auto">
                <pre><code set:html={codeContract} /></pre>
